<subSubSection pageId="191" pageNumber="192" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="191" pageNumber="192">
This species has an inflorescence of terminal heads like 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stocks, Hooker's J. Bot. Kew Gard. Misc. 4: 173. 1852. (Stocks" authorityYear="1852" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scindicus" order="Solanales" pageId="191" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scindicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="191" pageNumber="192">Convolvulus scindicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but lacks the reddish-brown hairs and the distinctive leaves of that species.
</paragraph>
